ZH: 尽管天气很热，但是我们还是要出门购物。
EN: Despite the hot weather, we still have to go shopping.

ZH: 尽管他很累，他仍然坚持健身。
EN: Despite being tired, he still insists on exercising.

ZH: 尽管你不同意，我还是希望你能支持我。
EN: Despite your disagreement, I still hope you can support me.

ZH: 尽管她很害怕，但她鼓起勇气登上了过山车。
EN: Despite being afraid, she gathered up the courage to ride the roller coaster.

ZH: 尽管他想睡觉，但他还是坚持完成了作业。
EN: Despite wanting to sleep, he still insisted on finishing the homework.

ZH: 他尽管年纪大了，但是身体还是非常健康。
EN: Despite his old age, his health is still very good.

ZH: 尽管他迟到了，他还是尽力赶到了会议室。
EN: Despite being late, he tried his best to reach the meeting room.

ZH: 尽管他很害羞，但他还是敢于表达自己的观点。
EN: Despite being shy, he dare to express his own opinions.

ZH: 尽管考试很难，他还是取得了好成绩。
EN: Despite the difficult exam, he still achieved good results.

ZH: 我尽管很累，但是我会努力工作到最后。
EN: Despite being tired, I will work hard until the end.

ZH: 尽管他第一次做菜，但是味道却非常美味。
EN: Despite cooking for the first time, the taste was still very delicious.

ZH: 尽管他很忙，但他还是抽出时间去参加聚会。
EN: Despite being busy, he still made time to attend the party.

ZH: 尽管他很聪明，但他仍然需要学习。
EN: Despite being intelligent, he still needs to study.

ZH: 尽管她害怕高处，但她还是勇敢地爬上了山顶。
EN: Despite being afraid of heights, she bravely climbed to the top of the mountain.

ZH: 尽管遇到困难，他还是坚持不懈地追求自己的梦想。
EN: Despite encountering difficulties, he still persevered in pursuing his dreams.

ZH: 这个项目尽管很复杂，我们还是要努力完成它。
EN: Despite the complexity of this project, we still have to work hard to complete it.

ZH: 这本书尽管很长，但是非常引人入胜。
EN: Despite being long, this book is very fascinating.

ZH: 这个城市尽管人口不多，但是发展迅速。
EN: Despite having a small population, this city is developing rapidly.

ZH: 尽管别人怀疑他，他仍然相信自己的能力。
EN: Despite others doubting him, he still believes in his own abilities.

ZH: 尽管路上堵车，我们还是及时赶到了机场。
EN: Despite the traffic jam on the road, we still arrived at the airport on time.

ZH: 尽管他不知道答案，但他还是勇于提问。
EN: Despite not knowing the answer, he still dares to ask questions.
